  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "We categorized components of each dataset as 'stable' or 'vulnerable' based on each subset's exposure to data poisoning.",
    "Specifically, datasets were deemed stable if their content was moderated through human oversight.",
    "The most significant driver of vulnerable content was web-scraped data, primarily the Common Crawl; however, even relatively 'stable' subsets like Wikipedia (users can edit most articles at will, rigorous moderation mitigates deliberate vandalism) have been proposed as attack substrates 6.",
    "By default, all tokens in OpenWebText, RefinedWeb and C4 were deemed vulnerable because these datasets consist entirely of web-scraped content.",
    "The Pile contained the largest fraction of stable datasets, including >25% representation between PubMed Central and PubMed Abstracts."
  ],
